    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the chips to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then<strong> </strong>drizzle over your <strong>red</strong> <strong>wine</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20-25 min \u2013 these are your <strong>salt & vinegar chips</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-fish-and-chip-pie-with-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir through your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>mustard stock</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-fish-and-chip-pie-with-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>mustard</strong> <strong>stock</strong> with your <strong>soft cheese</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[175ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> and\u00a0cook for 5-8 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-fish-and-chip-pie-with-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> chives</strong> finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-fish-and-chip-pie-with-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, remove the pan from heat and stir through the <strong>chopped chives</strong> and <strong>chopped basa</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy fish pie mix</strong></p><p>Transfer the<strong> creamy fish pie mix</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-fish-and-chip-pie-with-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the fish pie mix with the <strong>salt & vinegar chips</strong></p><p>Tip: Try to put the crispiest chips at the bottom and balance the rest over the top so that they don't sink!</p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chips are crispy and the fish is cooked through</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-fish-and-chip-pie-with-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pie is almost done, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 2-3 min or until tender</p><p>Once tender, drain the <strong>peas</strong> and return them to the pot with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-fish-and-chip-pie-with-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> creamy fish & chip pie</strong> with the<strong> peas</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
